  "prompt": "What are the recipes of five minutes easy to make snacks?",
  "response": "Here are some quick and easy snack recipes that can be prepared in about five minutes!\n\n### 1. **Peanut Butter Banana Toast**\n**Ingredients:**\n- 1 slice of whole-grain bread\n- 1 tablespoon peanut butter (or any nut butter)\n- \u00bd banana, sliced\n- A sprinkle of cinnamon (optional)\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Toast the slice of bread (if desired).\n2. Spread peanut butter on the toasted or untoasted bread.\n3. Top with banana slices.\n4. Sprinkle with cinnamon if you like, and enjoy!\n\n### 2. **Yogurt Parfait**\n**Ingredients:**\n- 1 cup Greek yogurt\n- \u00bd cup granola\n- \u00bd cup mixed berries (fresh or frozen)\n- A drizzle of honey (optional)\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. In a cup or bowl, layer \u00bd cup of Greek yogurt.\n2. Add a layer of granola and then a layer of mixed berries.\n3. Repeat the layers if desired, and drizzle with honey on top.\n\n### 3. **Avocado Toast**\n**Ingredients:**\n- 1 slice of bread\n- \u00bd ripe avocado\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Optional toppings (red pepper flakes, lemon juice, cherry tomatoes)\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Toast the slice of bread if desired.\n2. Mash the avocado in a bowl and season with salt and pepper.\n3. Spread the mashed avocado on the toast.\n4. Add any optional toppings, and enjoy!\n\n### 4. **Caprese Skewers**\n**Ingredients:**\n- Cherry tomatoes\n- Fresh mozzarella balls\n- Fresh basil leaves\n- Balsamic glaze (optional)\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. On a toothpick or small skewer, thread a cherry tomato, a basil leaf, and a mozzarella ball.\n2. Repeat until desired.\n3. Drizzle with balsamic glaze and season with salt and pepper before serving.\n\n### 5. **Hummus and Veggie Sticks**\n**Ingredients:**\n- \u00bd cup hummus\n- Assorted veggie sticks (carrots, cucumber, bell peppers, celery)\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Cut vegetables into sticks.\n2. Serve with hummus for dipping.\n\nThese snacks are not only quick to prepare, but they're also healthy and delicious! Enjoy!",
